OL,3,CTeachers and some NHS staff set for
OL,4,C5.5% pay rise
OL,6,FPublic sector pay rises well above the
OL,7,F3% expected by the Treasury will put
OL,8,Fextra pressure on spending under Ms
OL,9,FReeves' self-imposed fiscal rules,
OL,10,Fwhich include having debt falling as a
OL,11,Fshare of gross domestic product in
OL,12,Ffive years' time.
OL,14,FExtending the 5.5% pay boost ` which
OL,15,Fis above inflation at 2% ` to the
OL,16,Fentire public sector could cost some
OL,17,F#10 billion a year, according to the
OL,18,Finfluential Institute for Fiscal
OL,19,FStudies (IFS).
